41 (c) The total amount of matching grant funds provided by the State Board of Education
42 pursuant to this Code section shall not exceed $500,000.00 each state fiscal year.
43 (d) The State Board of Education is authorized to receive and administer federal funds to
44 provide matching grant funds pursuant to this Code section. The Department of Education
45 shall serve as a state level flow through point for any available federal funding.
46 (e) The State Board of Education shall prescribe criteria, policies, and standards deemed
47 necessary for the effective implementation of this Code section."
48 SECTION 2.
49 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
